# ChainView environment configuration.
#
# This file documents every CHAINVIEW_* variable the typed config surface reads
# (src/config.rs, docs/07-configuration.md §4). It lists variable NAMES only,
# never values — no secret is ever committed here. Precedence, highest first:
#
#     CLI flag  >  environment variable  >  config-file key  >  typed default
#
# Zero-config default: with none of these set, ChainView resolves to public
# Deribit BTC and needs no credentials at all (ADR-0003).
#
# `.env` in the working directory is loaded into the environment at startup.

# --- Global settings --------------------------------------------------------

# CHAINVIEW_PROVIDER      Provider id. default: deribit. Must match
#                         ^[a-z][a-z0-9_-]{1,31}$ and be registered.
# CHAINVIEW_UNDERLYING    Underlying ticker. default: BTC. Non-empty; upper-cased.
# CHAINVIEW_REFRESH       Chain refresh cadence (humantime, e.g. 2s).
#                         default: 2s. range: [250ms, 300s].
# CHAINVIEW_TICK          UI tick cadence (humantime, e.g. 250ms).
#                         default: 250ms. range: [50ms, 5s].
# CHAINVIEW_CHANNEL_CAP   Bounded channel capacity in messages.
#                         default: 1024. range: [64, 65536].
# CHAINVIEW_LOG_FILE      Log-file path (never stdout/stderr while the TUI runs).
#                         default: none (no file sink).
# CHAINVIEW_THEME         Color theme. default: auto. one of: auto | dark | light.
# NO_COLOR                Presence (non-empty) disables color. default: unset.

# --- Per-provider settings (<ID> = the env segment, docs/07 §5.1) -----------
#
# <ID> is the provider id transliterated to a shell-safe segment: uppercase,
# then '_' -> '__' and '-' -> '_'. Examples: deribit -> DERIBIT,
# my-broker -> MY_BROKER, my_broker -> MY__BROKER.

# CHAINVIEW_<ID>_ENDPOINT Upstream base URL override (absolute URL).
#                         default: none. e.g. CHAINVIEW_DERIBIT_ENDPOINT.
# CHAINVIEW_<ID>_REFRESH  Per-provider refresh cadence (humantime).
#                         default: inherits CHAINVIEW_REFRESH. range: [250ms, 300s].

# --- Credentials (ENVIRONMENT ONLY; never a file or flag; never logged) -----
#
# Read only from the environment per the provider's declared AuthKind
# (docs/07 §5, docs/SECURITY.md §1). A credential in a config file is rejected;
# a missing required credential names the provider, never the key. Deribit
# public data needs none. The keys below are NAMES only — never assign values
# here.
#
# CHAINVIEW_<ID>_TOKEN
# CHAINVIEW_<ID>_USERNAME
# CHAINVIEW_<ID>_PASSWORD
# CHAINVIEW_<ID>_API_KEY
# CHAINVIEW_<ID>_SECRET
#
# Concrete built-in examples (names only):
#   CHAINVIEW_IG_USERNAME
#   CHAINVIEW_IG_PASSWORD
#   CHAINVIEW_IG_API_KEY
#   CHAINVIEW_ALPACA_API_KEY
#   CHAINVIEW_ALPACA_SECRET
